<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFFB0147600EF47E90AF8E37" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFFB0147600EF47E90AF8E37" blockId="25.[828,1437,1150,1301]" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB0147600EF47E90CF8FB7" bold="true" box="[828,958,1150,1173]" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Comments.</emphasis>
I examined only photographs of the 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFFB0147660DF47E96ED8FB7" box="[1343,1436,1150,1173]" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFFB01476069F49E973C8F97" authorityName="Medvedev" authorityYear="2001" box="[859,1101,1182,1205]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicornuta">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB01476069F49E973C8F97" box="[859,1101,1182,1205]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Platyxantha bicornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on the structure of the aedeagus with a bifurcate apex I tentatively transfer it to 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFFB0147600EF4DE90C08FD7" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1865" box="[828,945,1246,1269]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hyphaenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB0147600EF4DE90C08FD7" box="[828,945,1246,1269]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Hyphaenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, further study is necessary to confirm this placement.
</paragraph>
